[UK statistics of _Mycobacterium bovis_ in various species present the following data in relation to cats for the 15 years from 1997 to 2011 (respectively): 0, 2, 0, 3, 0, 2, 2, 6, 13, 14, 15, 18, 26, 23, 18 (see at http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130315143000/http://www.defra.gov.uk/statistics/files/defra-stats-foodfarm-landuselivestock-tb-other-otherspecies-121102.xls).

Regarding previous decades/husbandry methods/production systems: according to Van der Hoeden (Zoonoses, Elsevier Publishing Company 1964; Tuberculosis, p. 28, table V, "The percentage of incidence of tuberculosis among dogs and cats admitted to veterinary clinics"), the following data were presented:
Place / years / dogs / cats
Berlin / 1925 / 0.3 / 2
Paris / 1927 / 5.6 / 13.5
Stockholm / 1928-37 / 2.5 / 4.8
Utrecht / 1926-44 / 1.03 / 4.66
Amsterdam and Leiden / 1942-44 / 1.5 / 11
London / 1940 / 1 / 3.6
Liverpool / 1949 / 6.5 / 13

The recent recurrence of _M. bovis_ in UK's cats since 2004/5, as indicated by Defra's statistics and exhaustively analysed by Gunn-Moore et al, is indeed a cause for concern. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1lNY.]
